INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("153", "1", "2013-12-22 18:00:54", "2013-12-22 18:00:54", "<strong>Privacy and Security Policy</strong>\r\n\r\nThis Privacy and Security Policy is provided for the benefit of existing customers of AbilityTrip, LLC (“AbilityTrip”) as well as other consumers and parties who seek information from or about AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n1.    OPENING STATEMENTS\r\n\r\n1.1    AbilityTrip Family\r\n\r\nThis Privacy and Security Policy governs the privacy and security practices of AbilityTrip; websites operated by AbilityTrip (including, but not limited to, www.AbilityTrip.com); and, companies owned by AbilityTrip and/or its principal shareholders.\r\n\r\n1.2    Applicability of Privacy and Security Policy\r\n\r\nOur Privacy and Security Policy applies to all individuals and entities from whom or for the benefit of whom we receive personally identifiable information (also commonly referred to as personally identifying information) (“PII”), whether the PII be collected through our corporate owned websites; traditional mailing and/or faxing channels; telephone or electronic communications; from some other medium; or from our clients.\r\n\r\n1.3    Our Commitment to Privacy\r\n\r\nAt AbilityTrip, we respect the privacy and the confidentiality of our customers’ information, particularly our customers’ personally identifiable information.  We are committed to keeping confidential the personally identifiable information you share with us.  We promise to use personally identifiable information only for the purpose for which it has been collected.  This Privacy and Security Policy explains how AbilityTrip collects, uses, discloses and protects the information we obtain.\r\n\r\n2.    PERSONAL INFORMATION COLLECTED AND HOW IT IS USED\r\n\r\n2.1    Personally Identifiable Information is any information that would, by itself, identify you or tend to identify you as a particular individual or entity.  This personally identifiable information may include, but not be limited to, your name, your address, credit card number, bank account information, and/or personal identification number (such as a social security number or driver’s license number).\r\n\r\n2.1.1    Personally identifiable information does not include any public information that is readily attainable through federal, state or local public record distribution channels.\r\n\r\n2.1.2    Personally identifiable information does not include any information that, by itself, could not identify you as a particular individual or entity.\r\n\r\n2.1.3    Personally identifiable information also does not include raw data that becomes aggregated for statistical purposes and cannot, thereafter, be identified with you as a unique individual or entity.\r\n\r\n2.2    Information Collected\r\n\r\n2.2.1    AbilityTrip collects information that is considered personally identifiable information and other information that, by itself, would not be considered personally identifiable information.\r\n\r\n2.2.2    Typically, AbilityTrip limits the personally identifiable information collected about an individual or entity to the individual’s or entity’s name, address, and electronic mail (“e-mail”) address.\r\n\r\n2.3    Collecting and Using Personal Information\r\n\r\n2.3.1    AbilityTrip will explain how it intends to use your personally identifiable information either before it collects the information (such as in this Privacy and Security Policy) or contemporaneously with the solicitation of such information about you.  Exceptions may exist where the intended use is obvious to a reasonable person.\r\n\r\n2.3.2    We will use the information collected only for the purposes explained to you.  Further, we limit the collection of personally identifiable information to only that information which is necessary for the purposes explained to you.\r\n\r\n2.3.3    Unless we are required to do so by law, we shall not obtain your consent before collecting personal identifying information about you from parties other than AbilityTrip.  Rather, AbilityTrip shall presume that you have previously provided such consent to any such third party from whom AbilityTrip obtains such information.\r\n\r\n2.3.4    AbilityTrip restricts the use of your personally identifiable information to AbilityTrip’s personnel.\r\n\r\n2.3.5    We shall not sell your personally identifiable information in the normal course of business operations.  Should the Website be sold, this paragraph shall not restrict the transfer of your personally identifiable information as part of the Website sold to a third party.\r\n\r\n2.3.5.    We may use your e-mail or regular mail address to send you communications about our company as well as to notify you of new services, new destination or travel information, or other information that we believe may be of interest to you. If you do not wish to receive electronic communications unrelated to your transactions with our company, you may “opt out” of the electronic distributions upon receipt of any such communication.  To discontinue receipt of traditional mail communications, or if you have any questions about our privacy practices, please contact our Privacy Officer directly (as provided below), or send a detailed e-mail to admin@abilitytrip.com.\r\n\r\n2.4    Disclosing Personal Information\r\n\r\n2.4.1    General.  AbilityTrip may provide your personally identifiable information to other persons, but only where we have your consent or where we have obtained information about you from a third party (presuming that you have previously provided such consent to any such third party from whom AbilityTrip obtains such information) or where we are required or permitted to do so by law.\r\n\r\n2.4.2    Strategic Partners.  AbilityTrip may employ, engage or retain certain trusted third parties (“Strategic Partners”) to perform functions and/or provide services on its behalf.  AbilityTrip will share personally identifiable information with these Strategic Partners only to the extent necessary to perform the functions and/or provide the services for which they have been employed, engaged or retained.  AbilityTrip shall also secure contractual obligations from our Strategic Partners to maintain the privacy and security of the PII shared with them.\r\n\r\n2.4.3    Business Transfers.  AbilityTrip reserves the right to sell, transfer or otherwise share some or all of its assets, including your personally identifiable information, in connection with a sale of assets; a merger, acquisition, or reorganization; or, filing for bankruptcy. You will have the opportunity to opt out of any such transfer if the planned processing of your information by the purchaser differs materially from that set forth in this Privacy and Security Policy.\r\n\r\n2.4.4    Legal Compliance. AbilityTrip may disclose any information about you to government or law enforcement officials or private parties as we, in our sole discretion, believe necessary or appropriate to respond to claims or legal process (including subpoenas); to protect the property and rights of AbilityTrip, its strategic partners or other third parties; to protect the safety of the public or any person; to prevent or stop any illegal, unethical, or legally actionable activity; or, generally, to comply with the law.\r\n\r\n2.5    Non-Personally Identifiable Information\r\n\r\n2.5.1    In addition to collecting personally identifiable information as previously described, AbilityTrip also collects other non-personally identifiable information.\r\n\r\n2.5.2    Non-personally identifiable information collected by AbilityTrip may be utilized without restriction.\r\n\r\n2.5.3    Although non-PII can be used in a number of ways, you can be assured that the use of the non-personally identifiable information cannot identify you as an individual or entity.\r\n\r\n2.5.4    Because non-PII cannot be used to identify you, AbilityTrip may in its discretion provide non-PII to other persons.\r\n\r\n2.6.    Information Obtained From Use of AbilityTrip’ Websites\r\n\r\n2.6.1.    Cookies\r\n\r\n2.6.1.1.    Cookies can be defined as bits of data stored on your computer that allow our website(s) to identify your browser and session.\r\n\r\n2.6.1.2.    AbilityTrip presently utilizes “Cookies”.\r\n\r\n2.6.1.3.    Cookies allow us to recognize certain information about you in an effort to provide an extra layer of security protection against unauthorized users. Based upon your web browser’s security settings, you have the ability to reject all cookies.\r\n\r\n2.6.1.4.    Unfortunately, disabling or rejecting Cookies may prevent you from accessing areas on AbilityTrip’s website, and could diminish your AbilityTrip experience.\r\n\r\n2.6.2.    IP Addresses\r\n\r\n2.6.2.1.    AbilityTrip maintains a log of your IP address when you access our corporately owned websites. This IP address by itself does not allow us to collect additional information about you.  However, it allows us to see which parts of the site you visit and how much time you spend browsing the site.\r\n\r\n2.6.2.2.    OTHER THAN YOUR IP ADDRESS, ABILITYTRIP DOES NOT DIRECTLY COLLECT ANY PERSONAL INFORMATION ABOUT YOU UNLESS YOU VOLUNTARILY PROVIDE US WITH THIS INFORMATION.\r\n\r\n2.7    Data Retention\r\n\r\n2.7.1.    The length of time for which AbilityTrip retains your PII and other information will vary depending on the nature of the services for which the information had been collected and the nature of the information.\r\n\r\n2.7.2.    Although this period may extend beyond the end of your relationship with AbilityTrip, it will be retained for only so long as necessary for AbilityTrip to respond to any issues arising from your relationship with AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n2.7.3.    When AbilityTrip no longer needs or requires your personal information, AbilityTrip will destroy, delete, erase or convert information to an anonymous form.\r\n\r\n3.    CONSENT\r\n\r\n3.1.    AbilityTrip may obtain your personal information through a variety of sources.  For each source or method, the manner of consent may differ.\r\n\r\n3.2.    In general, AbilityTrip operates on an “Opt-out” basis.  That is, AbilityTrip presumes that by accessing this website you have read this Privacy and Security Policy and AbilityTrip’s Terms and Conditions. Moreover, by providing the personal information requested (both personally identifiable and non-personally identifiable), you have consented to its use by AbilityTrip for the stated purposes.\r\n\r\n3.3.    For these reasons, unless and until you expressly inform AbilityTrip you do not wish your information to be used, AbilityTrip shall presume it has your consent.\r\n\r\n3.4.    Where AbilityTrip obtains information about a consumer from its customers or other third parties, AbilityTrip presumes that the consumer has previously provided appropriate consent to the party from whom AbilityTrip obtains the information.  In any case, the consumer can be assured that this Privacy and Security Policy applies to any information obtained from a third party.\r\n\r\n4.    ACCESS\r\n\r\n4.1.    Subject to certain limitations imposed by applicable privacy laws, you may request that AbilityTrip provide you with a copy of your personal information and/or information regarding how we have used that personal information.\r\n\r\n4.2.    Any such requests for such information should be directed to our Privacy Officer at the contact information provided below.\r\n\r\n4.3.    We will make every effort to respond to your request in a reasonable timeframe.\r\n\r\n5.    SECURITY\r\n\r\n5.1.    AbilityTrip takes the issue of protecting your personal information very seriously.  AbilityTrip protects the information it obtains about you with appropriate safeguards and security measures consistent with standard information practices. These measures include technical and procedural steps to protect your data from misuse, unauthorized access or disclosure, loss, alteration, or destruction.\r\n\r\n5.2.    For security purposes, AbilityTrip does not disclose all of its security measures.  Be assured that AbilityTrip does employ industry standard measures to protect your information.\r\n\r\n6.    DISCLAIMER AS TO THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES\r\nAlthough our corporate owned websites may contain links to other third-party websites, AbilityTrip is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of such websites and specifically disclaims any such responsibility.  AbilityTrip does not monitor the privacy practices or content of these websites.  If you have any questions about the privacy practices of a website other than an AbilityTrip owned website, you need to contact the Privacy Officer of the website about which you have a question.\r\n\r\n7.    REVISIONS TO PRIVACY AND SECURITY POLICY\r\n\r\n7.1.    AbilityTrip reserves the right to revise, amend, or modify this Privacy and Security Policy, our Terms and Conditions, and other online policies and agreements at any time and in any manner.\r\n\r\n7.2.    AbilityTrip shall provide notice of such changes by posting the revised policies to the applicable AbilityTrip owned websites, in addition to sending notice as provided and/or required by law.\r\n\r\n7.3.    With respect to this Privacy and Security Policy, you should visit our website at www.AbilityTrip.com from time to time to review the then-current terms.  At any time, the current-posted policies govern and shall be binding.\r\n\r\nFor Additional Information or Questions, Contact Our Privacy Officer AbilityTrip has a designated Privacy Officer in our Corporate Headquarters.  If you have additional questions or concerns regarding how AbilityTrip is managing or using your personal information, please send your concerns in writing to our Privacy Officer by e-mail, to faith.brehm@abilitytrip.com.", "Privacy policy", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "privacy-policy", "", "", "2013-12-22 18:01:00", "2013-12-22 18:01:00", "", "0", "http://abilitytripwp/?page_id=153", "0", "page", "", "0");
