INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("156", "1", "2013-12-22 18:01:33", "2013-12-22 18:01:33", "Ability Trip\r\n<strong>TERMS and CONDITIONS OF USE</strong>\r\n\r\nThese terms and conditions of use (“Terms and Conditions”) specified herein govern the use of www.abilitytrip.com (“Website”) and the services provided through the Website (“Website Services”) by AbilityTrip, LLC (“AbilityTrip”) that owns and operates the Website.  Please read these Terms and Conditions carefully.  By using the Website Services, you shall have affirmed consent to all of the Terms and Conditions specified herein and your agreement to be bound by them.  As such, these Terms and Conditions represent a binding agreement between you and AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n1.    General\r\n\r\n1.1    Definitions\r\n\r\n1.1.1    ”Consumer” means any individual or entity that visits the Website.  Where applicable, the term “Consumer” shall encompass all customers.\r\n\r\n1.1.2    ”Content” means all material, whether publicly posted or privately transmitted, that Customers upload, post, broadcast, email, transmit, or otherwise make available on the Website or through the Website Services.\r\n\r\n1.1.3    ”Customer” means any Consumer who uses the Website Services or registers with the Website.\r\n\r\n1.1.4    ”Customer Account” means the account created when a Customer creates a username and password and provides additional requested information to the Website in order to use the Website Services.\r\n\r\n1.1.5    ”AbilityTrip Forum” means any of the forums, discussion groups, or other areas in which you may post comments accessible via the World Wide Web at www.AbilityTrip.com.   The Website may refer to AbilityTrip Forum as “Discussions.”\r\n\r\n1.1.6    ”AbilityTrip Trademarks” means any trademarks, tradenames, logos, and other commercial designs of AbilityTrip or licensed to AbilityTrip, whether or not formal registration exists including, but not limited to, AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n1.1.7    ”Username” means the pseudonym or real name provided by a Customer when creating a Customer Account.  The Username will be the name visible to other Consumers and Customers of the Website and/or the Website Services.\r\n\r\n1.1.8    ”Website” means all of the information and content (in any format whatsoever) accessible through the World Wide Web at the address www.AbilityTrip.com.\r\n\r\n1.1.9    ”Website Material” means all of the information and content (in any format whatsoever) on the Website or transmitted via the Website Services.\r\n\r\n1.1.10    ”Website Services” means the services provided by AbilityTrip through www.AbilityTrip.com.\r\n\r\n1.2    By entering and using the Website and the Website Services, you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n1.3    All parties explicitly agree that the use of the Website and Website Services shall be pursuant to these Terms and Conditions.  AbilityTrip shall not be bound by any additional or different terms provided by any Consumer or Customer.\r\n\r\n1.4    The Terms and Conditions shall be considered and construed as a binding agreement between you and AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n1.5    The Terms and Conditions comprises the entire agreement between you and AbilityTrip, superseding any prior agreements.  Please note that you may be subject to additional rules and regulations that may apply when you apply for and use the Website Services.  Any such additional rules and regulations shall be explicitly referenced herein and considered as incorporated within the Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n1.6    These Terms and Conditions contain disclaimers (including Sections 7, 8, and 9) as well as exclusive remedy provisions (including Section 8).\r\n\r\n2.    Modifications to Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n2.1    Because the Internet remains a dynamic communications forum and the law on Internet and online commerce remain just as dynamic, the Parties understand that AbilityTrip may alter, amend, change, waive, terminate or modify any term contained within its Terms and Conditions at any time provided that:\r\n\r\n2.1.1    Should AbilityTrip alter, amend, change, waive, terminate or modify any term contained within these Terms and Conditions, it shall provide notice by:\r\n\r\n(a)    Posting the new Terms and Conditions to the Website, particularly http://www.abilitytrip.com/terms/\r\n\r\n(b)    electronic mail or other means pursuant to Section 10.10 of these Terms and Conditions; and/or\r\n\r\n(c)    as otherwise required by law.\r\n\r\n2.1.2    Upon Notice, any Customer may either elect to terminate use of the Website and Website Services, or to accept the altered, amended, changed, waived, terminated or modified Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n2.1.3    Should the Customer accept the altered, amended, changed, waived, terminated or modified Terms and Conditions, the Customer’s use of the Website and Website Services shall proceed under the new Terms and Conditions;\r\n\r\n2.1.4    Further, should the Customer accept the altered, amended, changed, waived, terminated or modified Terms and Conditions, the Customer shall execute any document presented to the Customer memorializing such acceptance.  However, the absence of such a document shall not affect the enforceability of, and AbilityTrip’s reliance upon, Customer’s acceptance.\r\n\r\n2.2    Apart from receiving notice from AbilityTrip, you agree to review the Terms and Conditions and the relevant rules and regulations periodically to be updated of any such changes.\r\n\r\n2.3    The act of placing a web page (URL) into a temporary file on your browser so that you may return to that page at a future date directly, without passing through certain preceding pages (“bookmarking”), may under certain circumstances result in the bypass of links to the Terms and Conditions.  You hereby agree that any use of such bookmarks or bookmarking to bypass any web pages to enter into the Website and Website Services constitutes acceptance of the Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n2.4    Please note that your continued use of the Website and Website Services following the changes of the Terms and Conditions constitutes acceptance of all such changes.\r\n\r\n3.    Intellectual Property Rights\r\n\r\n3.1    Copyright.  All of the Website Material is either owned by or licensed to AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n3.1.1    All Website Material is proprietary and constitutes valuable intellectual property.\r\n\r\n3.1.1.1    All Website Material is copyrighted and protected under treaty provisions and worldwide copyright laws.\r\n\r\n3.1.1.2    The Website Material, including that which is transmitted via the Website Services, may not be reproduced, copied, edited, published, transmitted or uploaded in any way without express written permission from AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n3.1.2    AbilityTrip provides a limited license to its Customers and Consumers to view, print, and download materials on the Website and/or through the Website Services for reasonable use and pursuant to these Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n3.1.3    By posting to and/or using AbilityTrip’s Website and Website Services, you grant AbilityTrip the world-wide, royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable, sub-licensable, and non-exclusive right to publish (via the Internet, in print, or via other methods) and to sub-license any Content that you provide or submit to the Website.\r\n\r\n3.1.4    By posting to and/or using AbilityTrip’s Website and Website Services, you agree that you shall not infringe the copyright of any third parties and shall indemnify AbilityTrip from any claims made by third parties against AbilityTrip including, but not limited to, copyright infringement.\r\n\r\n3.1.5    Customers may link to the Website from their own websites and other third party websites, if such link is otherwise in accordance with the Customer’s use of the Website Services and these Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n3.1.6    Customers and Consumers may not frame any elements of this Website within any other website.\r\n\r\n3.2    Trademarks.\r\n\r\n3.2.1    Nothing on the Website should be construed as granting, by implication, estoppel or otherwise, any license or right to use any of AbilityTrip Trademarks displayed on the Website without AbilityTrip’s prior express written permission.\r\n\r\n3.2.2    All goodwill generated from AbilityTrip Trademarks will inure solely to its benefit.\r\n\r\n3.2.3    All other companies’ names, brand names and product names are trademarks or trade names of their respective owners who may or may not endorse, be affiliated with or connected to AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n3.2.4    AbilityTrip reserves the right to restrict the use of its name, system, and logo.\r\n\r\n4.    Consumer Conduct\r\n\r\n4.1    The Website and Website Services shall be used for lawful purposes only.\r\n\r\n4.2    You agree to provide AbilityTrip with true, accurate and current information as requested when registering for Website Services from AbilityTrip.  Failure to do so shall constitute a breach of these Terms and Conditions.\r\n\r\n4.3    Every Customer chooses a password and screen name at time of registration.\r\n\r\n4.3.1      Please note that you should choose your name carefully and you may not choose or use a screen name of another person, a name that is violating a third party’s intellectual property rights, or a screen name that is offensive or inappropriate.\r\n\r\n4.4    You shall be solely and entirely responsible for any and all use of the Website and Website Services through your Customer Account.\r\n\r\n4.4.1    As a Customer, you may not permit any other person to use your Customer Account.\r\n\r\n4.4.2    Your Customer Account, Username and/or password (Login) may not be assigned or transferred to any other person or entity.\r\n\r\n4.4.3    You must promptly inform AbilityTrip of any apparent breach of security, such as loss, theft, or unauthorized disclosure or use of a Username or password.\r\n\r\n4.5    The Website and Website Services shall not be used for any of the following:\r\n\r\n4.5.1    Intentionally or unintentionally violating any applicable local, state, national, or international law, or any rules or regulations thereunder;\r\n\r\n4.5.2    Intentionally violating any intellectual property rights of a third party;\r\n\r\n4.5.3    Disseminating or posting harmful content including, without limitation, viruses, Trojan horses, worms, spyware, or any other computer programming routines that may damage, interfere with, secretly intercept, or seize any system, program, data, or personal information;\r\n\r\n4.5.4    Disseminating materials that are lewd, offensive, inflammatory, harassing, threatening, defamatory, or otherwise objectionable as determined by AbilityTrip in its sole discretion;\r\n\r\n4.5.5    Posting or transmitting, or causing to be posted or transmitted, via the Website or Website Services any spam;\r\n\r\n4.5.5.1    AbilityTrip maintains a strict policy forbidding any spam or misuse of email services within its Website or Website Services.\r\n\r\n4.5.6    Posting or transmitting, or causing to be posted or transmitted, via the Website or Website Services any materials advertising any business other than AbilityTrip;\r\n\r\n4.5.6.1    AbilityTrip may provide certain Customers an opportunity to advertise via the Website and/or Website Services after receiving express written permission from AbilityTrip.  For information regarding advertising, contact AbilityTrip via the contact form located at http://www.abilitytrip.com/contact/.\r\n\r\n4.5.6.2    Additional and/or different rules may apply in the event AbilityTrip dedicates a special forum in the future to the promotion and/or offering of services by Customers.\r\n\r\n4.5.6.3    The publication of customer reviews will not constitute advertising unless approved or generated by AbilityTrip.\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\">The publication of customer reviews will not constitute</div>\r\n<div id=\"_mcePaste\">&gt; advertising unless approved or generated by AbilityTrip.</div>\r\n4.5.6.4    AbilityTrip expressly forbids businesses from publishing reviews about themselves – real or fake – on AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n4.5.6.5    AbilityTrip expressly forbids businesses from publishing negative reviews about their competitors – real or fake – on AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n4.5.7    Seeking to obtain private financial information from any Consumer;\r\n\r\n4.5.8    To impersonate any other individual; and/or\r\n\r\n4.5.9    Attempting to interfere with AbilityTrip’s security measures.\r\n\r\n4.6    Should any Consumer believe that another individual has violated any of the foregoing terms and conditions, he/she should immediately notify AbilityTrip via http://www.abilitytrip.com/contact/.\r\n\r\n4.7    Upon learning of any error, omission or violation of the Terms and Conditions by any other third party, a customer shall immediately notify AbilityTrip via http://www.abilitytrip.com/contact/.\r\n\r\n4.8    Customers may delete their own comments.  Should Customers wish to delete a forum topic they have started, they may only delete their own posts in that topic.  Customers have no authority to delete the posts of other Customers.  Additionally, AbilityTrip reserves the right to and may in fact incorporate any comments posted by customers in other areas of the Website.  To remove a comment that has been incorporated by AbilityTrip, you will need to contact AbilityTrip at the contact below for purposes of requesting removal.\r\n\r\n4.9    Termination of Customer Account.\r\n\r\n4.9.1    AbilityTrip reserves the right to refuse its Website Services to anyone should it believe that the Website Services have been or are being used for any unlawful purpose.\r\n\r\n4.9.2    AbilityTrip reserves the right to take any further action as permitted by law should it believe that the Website Services have been or are being used for any unlawful purpose.\r\n\r\n4.9.3    In particular, AbilityTrip may terminate an account immediately should a party use the Website or Website Services for illegal purposes.\r\n\r\n4.9.4    Additionally, AbilityTrip may terminate an account immediately in the event that AbilityTrip believes, in its sole discretion, that a Customer is “flooding” the forums.\r\n\r\n4.9.5    AbilityTrip also reserves the right to suspend or terminate a Customer Account should AbilityTrip become involved in pending litigation or other similar dispute with the Customer, in relation to the Customer Account, or for any other reason.  Should the Customer become involved in litigation or other similar dispute in relation to the Customer Account, AbilityTrip also may suspend or terminate the Customer Account immediately and without notice.\r\n\r\n4.9.6    Should your account become terminated, you will remain solely responsible for all liabilities that may have arisen or arise from your Customer Account and/or the termination thereof.\r\n\r\n4.9.7    Any Customer whose account has been terminated by AbilityTrip may not access the Website or the Website Services without the prior express written permission of AbilityTrip\r\n\r\n4.9.8    Should the Website and/or Website Services become terminated or suspended, all Customer Accounts shall be terminated immediately, without any prior notifications by AbilityTrip.\r\n\r\n5.    Website Content.\r\n\r\n5.1    AbilityTrip does not endorse Content provided by Customers that is made available via the Website and/or Website Services.\r\n\r\n5.2    AbilityTrip reserves the right, but not the obligation, to delete posts that it believes, in its sole discretion, violate these Terms and Conditions.  The failure of AbilityTrip to delete any post does not constitute AbilityTrip’s endorsement of any such post.\r\n\r\n5.3    AbilityTrip is not responsible for any and all defamatory, libelous, or slanderous Content posted by its Customers.\r\n\r\n5.4    If you believe any Website Content violates your rights in any way, you may contact AbilityTrip via http://www.abilitytrip.com/contact.\r\n\r\n6.    DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTIES\r\n\r\n6.1    THE WEBSITE IS PROVIDED TO YOU “AS IS”, “WITH ALL FAULTS”, “AS AVAILABLE,” WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, TO THE FULLEST EXTENT POSSIBLE UNDER APPLICABLE LAW.\r\n\r\n6.2     ABILITYTRIP SPECIFICALLY DISCLAIMS ANY AND ALL WARRANTIES INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, THE FOLLOWING:\r\n\r\n6.2.1    ANY WARRANTIES CONCERNING THE AVAILABILITY, ACCURACY, RELIABILITY, COMPLETENESS, CAPABILITIES, SECURITY, TIMELINESS, USEFULNESS AND/OR CONTENT OF:\r\n\r\n6.2.1.1    THE WEBSITE/WEBSITE SERVICES; OR\r\n\r\n6.2.1.2    THE ABILITY OF THE WEBSITE/WEBSITE SERVICES TO INTEROPERATE OR INTEGRATE WITH ANY THIRD PARTY PRODUCTS SUCH AS SOFTWARE OR HARDWARE;\r\n\r\n6.2.2    ANY WARRANTIES RESULTING FROM A COURSE OF DEALING OR USAGE OF TRADE;\r\n\r\n6.2.3     ANY WARRANTIES WITH REGARD TO THE ACCURACY OR COMPLETENESS OF (OR ERRORS IN):\r\n\r\n6.2.3.1     THE CONTENTS;\r\n\r\n6.2.3.2     THE FUNCTIONING OF; OR,\r\n\r\n6.2.3.3    THE ACCURACY OF THE RESULTS OR OUTPUT THAT DERIVES FROM THE USE OF THE  WEBSITE/WEBSITE SERVICES;\r\n\r\n6.2.4    ANY WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE; AND\r\n\r\n6.2.5    ANY WARRANTIES REGARDING THE RIGHTS AND TITLE OF ABILITYTRIP IN THE WEBSITE/WEBSITE SERVICES, OR ANY WARRANTY THAT THE WEBSITE/WEBSITE SERVICES DOES NOT INFRINGE THE INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS OF A THIRD PARTY.\r\n\r\n6.3    WE ARE NOT LIABLE FOR ANY INFORMATION, SOFTWARE OR OTHER PRODUCTS THAT ARE DOWNLOADED FROM THE WEBSITE OR WEBSITE SERVICES BY YOU OR INSTALLED ON YOUR COMPUTER.\r\n\r\n6.4    THESE DISCLAIMERS APPLY TO ALL CONTENT AND MERCHANDISE ORDERED AND/OR PURCHASED FROM THE WEBSITE AND/OR WEBSITE SERVICES.\r\n\r\n7.    ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMERS\r\n\r\n7.1    Third Party Links and Products.\r\n\r\n7.1.1    IN CONNECTION WITH THE WEBSITE AND THE WEBSITE SERVICES, ABILITYTRIP MAY PROVIDE YOU WITH LINKS TO WEBSITES AND OFFERS FOR PRODUCTS AND SERVICES OF THIRD PARTIES.\r\n\r\n7.1.2    ABILITYTRIP HAS NO CONTROL OVER SUCH WEBSITES OR OVER SUCH PRODUCTS AND SERVICES.\r\n\r\n7.1.3    ABILITYTRIP IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR AND DOES NOT ENDORSE (A) THE CONTENT OF SUCH THIRD PARTY WEBSITES, (B) THE PRODUCTS OR SERVICES OFFERED BY SUCH THIRD PARTIES OR (C) THE PRIVACY AND OTHER PRACTICES OF SUCH THIRD PARTIES.\r\n\r\n7.1.4    ABILITYTRIP SPECIFICALLY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, RELATING TO THIRD PARTY PRODUCTS AND SERVICES INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, ALL IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NON-INFRINGEMENT, EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED IN THIS AGREEMENT OR WHERE SUCH DISCLAIMERS ARE HELD TO BE LEGALLY INVALID.\r\n\r\n7.1.5    SUCH THIRD PARTY WEBSITES MAY SOLICIT PERSONAL INFORMATION AND SEND COOKIES.  THE INCLUSION OF A LINK TO A THIRD PARTY WEBSITE ON THIS WEBSITE DOES NOT IMPLY ENDORSEMENT OF THE LINKED THIRD PARTY WEBSITE.\r\n\r\n7.1.6    ABILITYTRIP IS NOT RESPONSIBLE FOR THE AVAILABILITY OF SUCH WEBSITES OR PRODUCTS OR SERVICES OFFERED BY SUCH THIRD PARTIES.\r\n\r\n7.1.7    ABILITYTRIP SPECIFICALLY DISCLAIMS ANY LIABILITY FOR ITS CONSUMERS FAILING TO ABIDE BY THIRD-PARTY WEBSITES’ POLICIES AND TERMS.\r\n\r\n8.    LIMITATION OF LIABILITY\r\n\r\n8.1    IN NO EVENT WILL ABILITYTRIP; ITS OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, SHAREHOLDERS, AGENTS, REPRESENTATIVES, LICENSORS, SUCCESSORS OR ASSIGNS; OR ITS SUBSIDIARIES’/SUPPLIERS’ OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, SHAREHOLDERS, AGENTS, REPRESENTATIVES, LICENSORS, SUCCESSORS OR ASSIGNS, BE LIABLE TO YOU OR TO ANY THIRD PARTY WHATSOEVER FOR ANY DAMAGE, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, INDIRECT, DIRECT, SPECIAL, PUNITIVE, INCIDENTAL OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES (INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, DAMAGES FOR LOSS OF BUSINESS PROFITS, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, LOSS OR VANDALISM OR THEFT OF PROGRAMS OR INFORMATION, AND ANY OTHER KIND OF DAMAGE), OR ANY OTHER DAMAGES ARISING IN CONNECTION WITH OR IN ANY WAY OUT OF THE AVAILABILITY OR USE OF, RELIANCE ON, OR INABIL